ONE of the seven inmates who broke out of the Kutama
Sinthumule Correctional Centre outside Makhado in October 2017, has been
re-arrested. His arrest brings the total number of the recaptured fugitives to six, who broke out in October 2017. Phathutshedzo Nemadodzi was in jail for murder and robbery with
aggravating circumstances. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said Nemadodzi
aged who is from Dididi village outside Thohoyandou was apprehended while
hiding at his home. Ngoepe said a manhunt is still on for the remaining escapee
Raphael Nyota (30) who is from Harare in Zimbabwe. He was in prison for murder and robbery with aggravating
circumstances as well. â€œThe other five escapees who were re-arrested earlier include
Chris Faku aged (37), Jabulani Isaac Mahlangu (32) from Pretoria, Ntshengedzeni
Manukha (26) from Thohoyandou, Ntshavheni Thomas Munyai (30) from Riverside and
Justice Makamo (28) from Zimbabwe. Ngoepe urged anyone with information that can lead to the
re-arrest of the remaining fugitive contact Colonel Nyelisani Mabatha at 082
